97;206m (two hyphen-separated segments), so [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mparts[2:-1][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m returns the wrong substring; the get_item lookup silently misses, the demo masks it via the scan fallback, and a learner copying the helper carries the bug forward. The second WARNING is methodological: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mmatch_outcome[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m writes the per-pair CATE point estimate (a treatment-effect difference, e.g., [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mE[Y(GLP-1) - Y(SGLT2) | X] = -0.62[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m) into [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpredicted_outcome[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, then matches it against the patient's single-arm observed A1c change ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mY(GLP-1) = -1.62[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m) and feeds the pair into a "calibration" function that computes [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mmean_actual / mean_predicted[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m. Treatment effects and single-arm outcomes are not the same quantity, the pair-comparison the recipe emphasizes (target trial emulation, CATE estimation) is silently broken in the matching step, and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m_compute_calibration_from_pairs[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m amplifies the issue by reporting a slope that conflates the two. The third WARNING is that [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m_compute_agreement[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m picks the pair with the most-negative [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpoint_estimate[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m across pairs that have [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173mdifferent comparators[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;192;197;206m (GLP-1 vs SGLT2, GLP-1 vs sulfonylurea, SGLT2 vs sulfonylurea); the result is well-defined only when all pairs share a baseline, which they don't here, and the resulting "agrees with best es