[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion at chapter11.01-python-example.md uses correct boto3 API calls (bedrock-runtime.invoke_model with guardrailIdentifier/guardrailVersion, bedrock-agent-runtime.retrieve with proper retrievalConfiguration/vectorSearchConfiguration including numberOfResults/overrideSearchType/filter, dynamodb resource Table operations, events.put_events, firehose.put_record, cloudwatch.put_metric_data, adaptive retry Config). Error handling is thorough with try/except wrappers, structured logging, and comments explaining failure-mode rationale (capped retries for tight chat latency, non-blocking event/metric emission, fallback to 'clarify' on classifier failure, fallback to NO_INFORMATION on generation failure). The recipe pattern is demonstrated end-to-end across all eight pseudocode steps (receive/bootstrap, input screening for crisis/injection/PHI, scope classification with confidence threshold, KB retrieval with relevance threshold, grounded generation with citation discipline, output scope/grounding screening, delivery/logging, and audit archival via Firehose) and exercised by run_demo() with six representative scenarios (in-scope parking, in-scope insurance, crisis chest-pain, out-of-scope clinical, out-of-scope refill, prompt-injection). All pipeline functions are fully implemented; KB_PLACEHOLDER_ID/GUARDRAIL_PLACEHOLDER_ID are documented configuration values guarded by deploy-time assertions, and the mock clients at the end are explicitly labeled demo infrastructure with instructions to remove for real AWS — not stubs in the recipe logic itself."}[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h